claim.claim-text:
1. A medical procedure for stabilizing a patient's spine with an implant, the procedure comprising:
installing a first vertebral anchor into a first vertebra during a surgery;
installing a second vertebral anchor into a second vertebra during the surgery;
providing a flexible member having a flexibility, the flexible member including a first end, a second end and a length between the first end and the second end, a first portion of the flexible member being formed of a first material having a first elasticity and a second portion of the flexible member being formed of a second material having a second elasticity different from the first elasticity;
reducing the length of the flexible member to change the flexibility of the flexible member during the surgery, including making a cut at a longitudinal location along the flexible member such that the cut traverses both the first portion formed of the first material and the second portion formed of the second material; and
coupling the flexible member between the first vertebral anchor and the second vertebral anchor during the surgery.

9. A medical procedure for stabilizing a patient's spine with an implant, the procedure comprising:
installing a first vertebral anchor into a first vertebra during a surgery;
installing a second vertebral anchor into a second vertebra during the surgery;
providing a flexible member having a first end, a second end, a length between the first end and the second end and a longitudinal axis extending from the first end to the second end, a first portion of the flexible member being formed of a first material having a first elasticity and a second portion of the flexible member being formed of a second material having a second elasticity different from the first elasticity, wherein the flexible member has a first flexibility proximate the first end and a second flexibility proximate the second end, the first flexibility being different from the second flexibility;
separating the flexible member into at least a first section having the first flexibility and a second section having the second flexibility during the surgery, wherein each of the first section and the second section includes some of the first portion formed of the first material and some of the second portion formed of the second material; and
coupling the selected one of the first section and the second section of the flexible member between the first vertebral anchor and the second vertebral anchor during the surgery.
